body:
@Jackie-Jiang So, our new approach should be:

- Block IS update if it violates the instance mapping. Emit metrics + setup alert for observability. 

Is my understanding correct? It sounds good to me.

@Jackie-Jiang we need protection on both sides. Ensuring IS is always correct is not enough. The routing happens based on the current state and EV and the change is not atomic.

Also, there are many scenarios where a segment on a particular node will become offline or ERROR etc. We dont want be coding for every scenario instead we need to code for the invariant that a server instance should own all the segments belonging to a partition to be eligible to serve the query.

+1 from my side on the idea. I haven't reviewed the code.

